<h1>7. API Reference</h1>
<h2>7.1 PHP</h2>
<pre>OraBooks_Workflow::transition('invoice', $invoice_id, 'cancel', [
    'user_id' => $user_id,
    'org_id'  => $org_id,
    'reason'  => 'Customer request',
]);

OraBooks_Workflow::allowed_events('bill', 'submitted');
// Returns: ['approve', 'void']</pre>

<h2>7.2 AJAX Endpoints</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Action</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_workflow_transitions</td><td>Transition history for a record</td></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_workflow_allowed_events</td><td>Allowed events from current state</td></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_workflow_transition</td><td>Execute transition (guarded)</td></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_workflow_health</td><td>Org workflow health snapshot</td></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_invoice_cancel</td><td>Cancel draft/sent invoice</td></tr>
<tr><td>orabooks_bill_void</td><td>Void draft/submitted/approved bill</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7.3 REST API</h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> POST /wp-json/api/internal/state/transition</p>
<p><strong>Headers:</strong> X-OraBooks-Org-Id: {org_id}, Authorization (JWT)</p>
<p><strong>Body:</strong> record_type, record_id, event, reason (optional), mfa_otp (optional)</p>
<p><strong>Permission:</strong> manage_settings OR submit_transaction OR approve_journal</p>

<h1>8. Cross-Cutting Integration</h1>
<h2>8.1 Audit (SL-009)</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Event</th><th>When</th></tr>
<tr><td>state_changed</td><td>Successful transition</td></tr>
<tr><td>invalid_state_transition</td><td>Rejected transition (409)</td></tr>
<tr><td>workflow_transition_failed</td><td>Precondition or publish failure</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>8.2 Event Bus (SL-302)</h2>
<p>Publishes <code>state_transition</code> with: org_id, record_type, record_id, event, from_state, to_state</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>workflow_read_model</strong> — bumps read-model dues counters</li>
<li><strong>workflow_notifications</strong> — org admin notifications (non-journal)</li>
<li><strong>job_enqueue_bridge</strong> — async webhook dispatch</li>
</ul>

<h2>8.3 RBAC and MFA (SL-003 / SL-002)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Journal: submit/approve/reject/post/reverse permissions + fiscal period checks</li>
<li>Journal approve: maker-checker + MFA for high-value (centralized preconditions)</li>
<li>Expense: manage_expenses / approve_expense per event</li>
<li>Invoice/Bill: create_invoice / manage_settings; cancel and void guarded</li>
</ul>

<h2>8.4 Observability (SL-093)</h2>
<ul>
<li>workflow.transition_success_24h / workflow.transition_failure_24h</li>
<li>Dashboards: /observability (org) and /admin/observability (platform)</li>
</ul>

<h1>9. Database</h1>
<p><strong>Table:</strong> wp_orabooks_state_machine_transitions</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Column</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>org_id</td><td>Tenant traceability</td></tr>
<tr><td>record_type</td><td>journal, invoice, bill, expense, commission</td></tr>
<tr><td>record_id</td><td>Business record primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td>from_state / to_state</td><td>State change</td></tr>
<tr><td>event</td><td>Triggering event name</td></tr>
<tr><td>triggered_by</td><td>User ID</td></tr>
<tr><td>reason</td><td>Optional free text</td></tr>
<tr><td>created_at</td><td>Timestamp</td></tr>
</table>

<h1>10. Business Rules — Cancel and Void</h1>
<h2>Invoice Cancel</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Rule</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
<tr><td>Allowed states</td><td>draft, sent</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blocked if</td><td>paid, partial, or paid_amount &gt; 0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Side effect</td><td>Sets payment_status = cancelled</td></tr>
<tr><td>Posted invoices</td><td>Cannot cancel</td></tr>
</table>
<h2>Bill Void</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Rule</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
<tr><td>Allowed states</td><td>draft, submitted, approved</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blocked if</td><td>paid, partial, or paid_amount &gt; 0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Posted bills</td><td>Cannot void</td></tr>
</table>

